  "bio_raw": "Arwin Ahmad a Mass Communication and Journalism graduate with a Master's degree in the same field. She is currently a lecturer at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh, where she teaches and mentor students pursuing a similar career path.\nBefore joining academia, Arwin Ahmad worked with DW Akademie as a researcher, focusing on Constructive Journalism, a new concept introduced by DW. Additionally, She worked as an assistant Gender Analyst at the Bangladesh Bondhu Foundation, where she had the opportunity to interview local women from poverty-stricken families to advocate for their rights and address their needs. This experience gave me a unique perspective on life and a greater understanding of the role of media in shaping society.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Curriculum, Educational Management, Interpersonal Communication, Gender, Art."
  ],
